sec.p:
To quantify individual learning rates, we computed the slope of performance as a function of training day for each animal. For each mouse, performance values (proportion of correct choices) were regressed against each Day using a simple linear regression model:
Performanceanimal=β0+β1∗Day \begin{document}$$\displaystyle \text{Performance}_{\text{animal }}=\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}{*}\text{Day}$$\end{document}
The slope (β₁) provides an estimate of the rate of improvement per training day.
